# KiCI quickstart — environment template.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in the three KICI_* values below.
# `docker compose` reads `.env` automatically from the current directory.

# ── 1. Orchestrator registration token (from app.kici.dev) ─────────────────
# Created under "Settings → Orchestrators → New" in the KiCI dashboard.
# Authorises this orchestrator to connect to the public Platform relay.
KICI_PLATFORM_TOKEN=replace-me-with-the-token-from-app-kici-dev

# ── 2. PostgreSQL password (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Defaults to the local-only stub `kici-local` (Postgres isn't published
# outside the compose network, so a known stub is safe). Uncomment and set a
# value only if you want a custom password.
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=replace-me-with-a-random-postgres-password

# ── 3. Orchestrator secret-encryption key ─────────────────────────────────
# 64-character hex string. Encrypts source credentials, workflow secrets,
# and join tokens at rest in the orchestrator database. Treat as a master
# key — losing it means losing every encrypted record.
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
KICI_SECRET_KEY=replace-me-with-a-64-char-hex-string

# ── 4. Bootstrap admin token ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# First-time admin token for `kici-admin` CLI calls against this
# orchestrator. Used to register the GitHub App and provision per-source
# secrets. Rotate or revoke from `kici-admin token` once the dashboard is
# wired up. Any opaque random string; the orchestrator hashes it on first
# use.
# Suggested: openssl rand -hex 32
KICI_BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_TOKEN=replace-me-with-a-bootstrap-admin-token

# ── SeaweedFS (object storage) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# The stack includes a self-contained SeaweedFS S3 service so `kici run remote`
# works out of the box (it uploads your working tree to object storage for the
# agent to fetch). No configuration needed — credentials are fixed local-only
# constants in docker-compose.yaml. Data persists in the `seaweedfs-data`
# volume. See docs: user/quickstart/compose — "run a workflow without pushing".
